</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3803"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3803-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3803">Code of ethics for secrecy classification&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/7602-4049">vfdean</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">3 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">A public code of ethics with regard to classifying government data or actions as secret should be developed.  Acceptable instances of such classification should be defined as specifically as possible (e.g., "to preserve national security" is too general). Then review of the classification of specific data as secret by other government classifiers should always be done in order to ensure that the ethics code is upheld.  Secret actions or data that might be considered as violating civil rights or liberties should receive extra review and consideration before being approved.  One goal of the ethics code should be to minimize data that is classified as secret. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3803" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3803', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=3803')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3803"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=secrecy">secrecy</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=national security">national security</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3803"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
