<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/7533-4049">kehoefl</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">3 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Your campaign promises included making your administration more open by posting bills, etc on the internet where it could be viewed by the American People.<br/>I must say that on a couple of occassions I have checked the website to be able to check out a bill that was coming up for discussion or a vote, but could not find it there.  <br/>A prime example was the Stimulus Bill, which was voted on quickly and it did not allow the public to review it, much less have an opportunity to voice their concerns.<br/>I would like to see you keep your promise to make your administration more transparent by have the items posted where they can be reviewed.<br/></div>
