<div id="Idea_3711"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3711-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3711">Put a Face on the Bureaucrats--Give Them Facebook Pages&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4312-4049">bharshaw</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">3 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Give each Federal bureaucrat his or her own Facebook(-type) page. Any member of the public can look up the local postman, any member of the bureaucracy can look up the person he's dealing with at a sister agency, etc. and enter messages, provide feedback and evaluations, ask questions.  </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3711" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3711', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=3711')">Comments (5)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3711"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3711"></div>
